prompts.frontCover:
Greeting card front cover, humorous and minimalist design. A cartoon illustrated version of Jordan (from photo, left) and Lao Lao (from photo, right) are hilariously trying to balance on a giant snowboard that is speeding down a snowy mountain slope. The snowboard is creatively designed to look like a piece of wagyu steak, complete with marbling patterns.

Jordan is at the front of the "wagyu snowboard," laughing with a joyful expression. He's wearing the dark navy t-shirt from the photo. Instead of snowboard bindings, his feet are comically stuck in two large Chinese takeout boxes. He's holding oversized chopsticks as if they were ski poles.

Lao Lao is sitting behind him on the snowboard, wearing the white zip-up jacket from the photo, holding on tightly to his shoulders with a look of playful panic.

Instead of regular snow, they are snowboarding on a "mountain" made of white rice. Scattered around the rice slope are minimalist, 2D icons of sushi rolls (tuna maki, salmon nigiri) acting as obstacles like trees or rocks. In the background, simple binary code (0s and 1s) streams down like falling snow against a clean, solid light-blue sky.

The overall style is flat 2D vector art with clean lines, simple shapes, and a limited color palette focusing on whites, reds of the wagyu, and the colors of their clothing.

Centered in the clean space above them, the text reads "Happy Birthday, Jordan!" in a beautiful, readable, elegant handwritten cursive script.
